# ============================================================================
# staqpaq — .env.example  (committed; copy to .env.local before building)
# ============================================================================
#
# staqpaq has NO required runtime environment variables.
#
# Why this file is (intentionally) empty of secrets:
#   - Persistence is browser-local (IndexedDB via idb-keyval) — no database
#     connection string, no host, no credentials.            [service-map.yaml]
#   - The archiver (fflate) runs entirely client-side — no API key.
#                                                            [service-map.yaml]
#   - Hosting is static (GitHub Pages / any static host) — no server runtime,
#     no backend, no deploy token consumed by the app itself.      [stack.yaml]
#   - There are no user accounts, third-party APIs, or paid services bound to
#     this build, so there is nothing to authenticate.    [capabilities.yaml]
#
# Because the persistence provider contributes no connection variables and no
# service is bound that requires credentials, there are no entries to fill in.
# Copying this file is still part of the standard setup loop so the build
# scaffold is uniform across local static app projects:
#
#     cp .env.example .env.local
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# IMPORTANT — do not confuse this file with the pack staqpaq PRODUCES.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# One of staqpaq's capabilities (export_pack) DERIVES a `.env.example` as part
# of the build pack it emits for the user's *configured* app. That generated
# file describes the implied environment variables of whatever the user
# selected, and it is a product OUTPUT — it has nothing to do with running
# staqpaq itself. This file (the one you are reading) governs the staqpaq repo;
# the generated one travels inside the exported pack.        [snag-list.md S4]
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# If a future change binds a real service (e.g. a remote sync backend, noted as
# an open question, not in MVP), add ONE line per variable here with a safe
# placeholder and a one-line comment (purpose · source · build-time vs runtime).
# Never commit a real secret value to this file.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# (no runtime environment variables required)
